@node Usage "Usage"

 Arguments
 =========

 Syntax: FreeFreq NODE,OUTBOUND/K,NODELIST/K,PUBSCREEN=PS/K,DEFNODE/K,
         CALLPORT/K

 NODE       The default node to appear in the node gadget in FreeFreq.
            This is optional.

 OUTBOUND   The directory where FreeFreq tries to create the *.REQ files.
            Default: MAIL:Outbound

 NODELIST   The directory where FreeFreq tries to open the nodelist.
            Default: NODELIST:

 PUBSCREEN  The public screen where FreeFreq tries to open its window.
            Default: Workbench

 DEFNODE    The default node that FreeFreq uses to expand incomplete
            node numbers. If you for example have "2:200/207.0" as
            default node, "100" would be expanded to "2:200/100.0"

 CALLPORT   If this is specified, FreeFreq will put an extra gadget
            in its window marked "Call". If you press that window,
            FreeFreq will save the request and try to call that node
            immediately. Here you should specify the name of an Arexx
            port that understands the command "CALL <node>", for
            example TrapDoor or why not TrapDispatcher?

 You can also use all these keywords as Workbench tooltypes.

 Use with TrapDispatcher:
 ========================
 Put this line in TrapDispatcher.prefs:

 External "@RFile Request" "MAIL:FreeFreq PS TRAPDOOR DEFNODE 2:200/207 CALLPORT TRAPDISPATCHER"

 You might want to replace 2:200/207 with something that is more convenient to you, such as
 your node or your boss if you are a point.

 FreeFreq window
 ===============
 Enter the node that you want to request files from in the "Node" string
 gadget. In the text gadget just below, FreeFreq will show you the name
 of the BBS and the name of the sysop. Enter the files you want to request
 one by one in the gadget below the list. If you want to delete a file
 from the list, just select it, clear the listview, press return and
 the file will disappear from the list.

 When you are finished and want to save the request, press Ok. If you have
 specified CALLPORT, there is also a gadget marked Call. If you press that
 gadget, FreeFreq will save the request and then send a CALL command to the
 ARexx port you have specified

 If you don't want to save the request, press Cancel.

 Hotkeys in FreeFreq
 ===================
 You can use the Up and Down keys to control the list gadget where the
 filenames are displayed.  All hotkeys can be accessed when ehen you are in
 a string gadget if  you hold down the right Amiga key and press the hotkey.

@endnode

